      <Meanings>
        <Meaning id="591cdb23-0131-4438-878f-a09bc076088d" type="Noun">
          <Vi>Natri</Vi>
          <En>A soft, silvery-white, highly reactive metallic element (symbol Na) essential for nerve function and fluid balance in the body.</En>
          <Example>Sodium is a key component of table salt (sodium chloride).</Example>
          <IsArchaic>false</IsArchaic>
          <Situations>
            <Situation id="da8bf160-9597-4dae-9657-70ae7378f032">
              <Vi>Trong hóa học, natri là một kim loại kiềm phản ứng mạnh với nước.</Vi>
              <En>In chemistry, sodium is an alkali metal that reacts vigorously with water.</En>
            </Situation>
            <Situation id="8c96e198-89ee-41ab-86fb-cdd0f5f9e939">
              <Vi>Bác sĩ thường khuyên giảm lượng natri trong chế độ ăn để kiểm soát huyết áp.</Vi>
              <En>Doctors often advise reducing sodium intake in the diet to manage blood pressure.</En>
            </Situation>
          </Situations>
        </Meaning>
